%h4.mt-4
  Supporting inclusive and sustainable research infrastructure for systematics (SISRIS)
%p
  %img{src: "/images/sisris.jpg", alt: "SISRIS logo", class:"img-fluid pull-left float-left mr-2", width: "150px", height: "150px"}
  Supported by a conference grant from the US National Science Foundation to Dr. Andrea Weeks (George Mason University; Ted R. Bradley Herbarium), and Drs. Shawn Zeringue-Krosnick and Twanelle Majors (Tennessee Tech University; Hollister Herbarium). It supports two US-based workshops and symposia at the 2023 annual meetings of the 
  %a{href: "https://www.sebiologists.org/asb-2023.html"} Association of Southeastern Biologists
  and
  = succeed "." do
    %a{href: "https://2023.botanyconference.org/"} Botany 2023
  The purpose of the work is to share new practices that improve attribution of natural history specimens and highlight research advances in systematics that can be made as a consequence of improved people-data within biodiversity informatics databases.
